RMP threshold levels.

The power plant is not subject to 29 CFR 1910.119, the Process Safety Management (PSM) Standard because the aqueous ammonia concentration (29.4 percent by weight) is below the PSM threshold of 44 percent by weight.  The facility is classified as NAICS Code 221112, Fossil Fuel Electric Power Generation.  This set of conditions dictates Prevention Program Level 2 applicability under the RMP regulation.

GENERAL ACCIDENTAL RELEASE PREVENTION PROGRAM 

The AES Ironwood Power Plant implements management systems and practices that meet or exceed RMP Level 2 Prevention Program requirements.  These requirements are defined according to the following elements:

- Safety information;

- Hazard review;

- Operating procedures;

- Training;

- Maintenance;

- Compliance audits; and

- Incident investigation.

The requirements of these elements are met or exceeded through implementation of safety procedures and safety management systems.  These programs are embodied in written documentation as well as continual training and awareness programs to reinforce the importance of facility safety.  Highlights of these policies and procedures are as follows:

- Information regarding chemical and other hazards is incorporated into site training programs, is well understood, and continually reinforced with employees and contractors;

- The ammonia system is subjected to periodic, detailed Hazard Reviews to identify hazards, safeguards, and opportunities for improved ammonia risk management;

- Operations of all aspects of the facility are controlled through written procedures which are arranged to ensure the safe operation of the plant, including steps needed to control hazards in the event of an abnormal conditions;

- All personnel involved with operating or maintaining the facility are thoroughly trained and qualified through formal qualification programs;

